    • takeFromInventory

      public static Map<ItemStack,Integer> takeFromInventory(EntityPlayerMP player, Predicate<ItemStack> predicate, boolean simulate, int count)
      take count amount of stacks that matches given filter. might take partial amount of stuff, so simulation is suggested if you ever need to take more than one.
      Parameters:
      player - source of stacks
      predicate - item stack filter
      simulate - whether to do removal
      count - let's hope int size is enough...
      Returns:
      amount taken. never negative nor bigger than count...

    • takeFromInventory

      public static int takeFromInventory(EntityPlayerMP player, ItemStack filter, boolean simulate)
      take count amount of stacks that matches given filter. might take partial amount of stuff, so simulation is suggested if you ever need to take more than one.
      Parameters:
      player - source of stacks
      filter - the precise type of item to extract. stackSize matters
      simulate - whether to do removal
      Returns:
      amount taken. never negative nor bigger than count...

    • takeFromInventory

      public static Map<ItemStack,Integer> takeFromInventory(Iterable<ItemStack> inv, Predicate<ItemStack> predicate, boolean simulate, int count, boolean recursive)
      take count amount of stacks that matches given filter. Will do 1 level of recursion to try find more stacks.... e.g. from backpacks...
      Parameters:
      inv - source of stacks
      predicate - item stack filter
      simulate - whether to do removal
      count - let's hope int size is enough...
      recursive - do recursive lookup using stack extractors
      Returns:
      amount taken. never negative nor bigger than count...
